title.29: Marvel Graphic Novel: Emperor Doom (Trade Paperback)

description.0: The West Coast Avengers trip through time continues. Can they survive the Wild Wild West?
description.2: When the Clinic hires freelance bounty hunters, they'll divide and conquer the D.P.7!
description.3: Classic X-Men, reprinted in style! This blockbuster issue remasters and retells the unforgettable story of Uncanny X-Men #100, in which Jean Greay makes the untilate sacrifice to save her X-Men family from a cosmic death in the stars!
description.4: The holiday season usually brings about cheer...but not this year. Tyrone reunites with his family for the season, and Psi-Force pays a dear price on this little trip.
description.5: A new villain leads Daredevil on a wild Christmas Eve chase!
description.6: A psychic villain has been attacking minds at the Gamma Base. An unlikely member of the team risks his life for Bruce.
description.7: The founding of Stark Enterprises! Tony doesn't celebrate the expansion of his company for very long; he is attacked by a strange being called the Adaptoid, who is sent by none other than Stark's main competitor, Justin Hammer.
description.8: Iceman of the X-Men, prisoner of Loki! The Frost Giants attack, staking their claim over one of Midgard's mutants. Balder faces his own woes, while all of Asgard succumbs to a mysterious illness. But what disease can possibly kill immortals?
description.12: Captured by the Wizard! The sinister scientist has taken the Thing and Franklin Richards captive, and with the Torch on his honeymoon, only Reed and Susan are left to stop him!
description.13: Storm is being hunted by the old World War 2 heroes she encountered in the last issue. In open combat, she has no chance. To defeat them she will have to outsmart them.
description.18: At the end of their rope, the X-Men continue to solicit help from none other than...Doctor Doom! But what will Kitty have to say about all this?
description.19: In his absence, Sergeant Polkow assigns his clerk, Rob Little, to the field!
description.20: GANG WAR PART 4 Daredevil and Spidey come to blows over their failed midnight meet-up, especially when Spider-Man disagrees with DD's methods for taking down Kingpin. The trail towards Kingpin leads ever closer to his demise- how will Wilson Fisk escape the Gang War?
description.21: She-Hulk pays a long overdue visit to the Avengers Hydrobase, but her arrival coincides with an attack from Tyrak! Following the battle, Wasp nominates Dr. Druid for Avengers membership and steps down as chairwoman to take a formal leave of absence.
description.22: What plan is the Power Broker forming and can D-Man help Captain America stop him?
description.30: Cannonball, Warlock, Cypher and Mirage make shocking discoveries when they run into Katie Powers of the future.
description.32: It's a blast to the past as the West Coast Avengers find themselves in the Wild West and meet up with Rawhide Kid, Two-Gun Kid and more!
description.34: GANG WAR PART 3 Is Daredevil in danger? The war on the streets revs up, as The Rose makes a disastrous choice while escaping police. MJ delivers a message to Spider-Man all too late. The NYPD may be involved, but are they enough to quell the violence?
description.35: The flag-flying Super Patriot returns! Can even Captain America stop the Super Patriot's maniacal manipulation of the American Dream at a benefit rock concert?
description.36: Daredevil continues to try and end a serial killer's reign of terror, but things get worse and worse for Daredevil and the city itself!
description.37: Rick Jones seeks solace in Bruce Banner's old hideout. Can a Hulked-out Rick take on S.H.I.E.L.D. alone?
description.38: Tony Stark and Rhodey don their Iron Man armor for their final battle against the hordes of A.I.M. For one person, the battle ends in death!
description.39: The Old Man who granted Ken the power of the Star Brand is back- and plans on taking Ken with him...to SPACE! He leaves Ken Connell with a simple choice: come with me or prepare for battle!
description.40: Thor, weakened from his previous battles, is ambushed by Dark Elves! But when Thor loses the will to fight, he finds rescue in the form of an uncanny ally!
description.44: Storm battles against the likes of Stonewall, Super Sabre, and Crimson Commando!
description.52: Scuzz has had enough and he's leaving the rest of D.P.7!
description.53: The Hellfire Club's internal strife is spotlighted in ""Out with the Old!""
description.54: The Psi-Force has a new enemy to look out for. His name is Thomas Boyd and he has permission to capture the members...dead or alive.
description.56: Tempers flare when the outlawed mutants become outraged at Reed Richard's refusal to help Kitty Pryde! A depowered Storm takes a serious beating. Maybe Franklin Richards' prophetic dreams hold a grain of truth?
description.57: A news correspondent accompanies the soldiers on a mission that goes wrong right from the start.
description.58: Ozzy Ostrich's hardcore concert leaves Peter less than impressed...especially when Spider-Ham uncovers Ozzy's plot to hypnotize the audience with his gnarly guitar playing!
description.59: Karma, Magma, Wolfsbane and Sunspot are stuck in the future…where they are being hunted by Sentinels!
description.61: The Desert Dwellers set up an ambush for the West Coast Avengers!
description.64: The D.P.7 are on the run, but what super-powered tricks does the Clinic have to track them down?
description.65: Jean Grey dives deep into her history and love for Cyclops in ""A Love Story!""
description.66: The might of the Psi-Hawk lingers as Kathy must find a way to harness her powers and defeat him!
description.67: There’s a killer who’s leaving the streets red with blood and the police can’t seem to get a lead. Can Daredevil stop the slasher before the city tears itself apart?
description.68: Bruce Banner is once again battling his greatest enemy- his own mind.
description.69: A.I.M. plots revenge against Tony Stark, and the consequences might mean the end of Iron Man! A simple plot becomes a reality when an A.I.M. suicide team hijacks Tony and Rhodey's space shuttle and sabotages the new Stark International Space Station.
description.70: Ken discovers that what he thought were pranks from college kids were actually Libyan terrorists trying to lure him! Can he make it to Libya before they catch wind of the ruse? Meanwhile, how will Debbie handle the shocking news Ken's about to throw her way?
description.71: Thor does the unthinkable! Fighting another mortal he is hypnotized to see as a foe, Thor mistakenly kills them - for the whole world to see! Now with foes and the media alike after Thor, Loki is free to enact his latest scheme on Asgard!
description.75: Tensions run high when Johnny asks Thing to be the best man at his wedding to Alicia Masters. The only problem? Alicia is Ben's ex!
description.83: GANG WAR PART 2 Enter The Punisher! Frank Castle has his own reasons for wanting to eliminate Hobgoblin and the other mob bosses. But are his measures too extreme for Spider-Man? Spidey, caught in the crossfire of The Punisher's rage!
description.84: Cap's investigation of the Red Skull's house unleashes all the guilt and secret fears Captain America never before faced! Will the trauma of what he sees and experiences in the house destroy Captain America?
description.86: Jenny Swensen is in jail for murder! Two of the Troubleshooters are determined to break her out! And why is Kenneth Connell— better known as Star Brand— involved in this story?
description.87: Wolverine and Spider-Man are both in Germany in a race to save Charlemagne, Wolverine's close friend.
description.89: Following the horror of the Mutant Massacre, the X-Men turn to the Fantastic Four seeking aid for their youngest member -- Kitty Pryde's mutant ability to phase through solid matter is now threatening her life!
description.90: Ed, Mike, and Lonnie get furlough passes to Saigon, but the big city can be just as dangerous as the combat zone.
description.91: The Fearsome Fate of Franklin Richards -- at the hands of Doctor Doom!
description.92: The Grandmaster is back, and he has created a brand new Contest of Champions! In one corner - Earth's Mightiest Heroes, the Avengers! In the other - the horrible Legion of the Unliving!
description.94: From the pages of AVENGERS, the New Masters of Evil! A call for help from the original Yellowjacket plunges Hellcat and Tigra into the most shocking rescue mission of their lives.
description.97: Trying to escape Magus, Illyana teleports the New Mutants to ancient Scotland! Now, the teenaged mutants are caught up in knightly duels between the Scottish and English!
description.98: The Jade Giant battles the combined might of two deadly enemies! Can Hulk defeat Zzzax and the Rick Jones/Hulk hybrid? Or is it too much for one beast to bear?
description.99: This pulse-pounding tie-in with the Avengers finds Spider-Woman stalked by a trio of high-tech bounty hunters. Will Iron Man reach her before it's too late?

16.text: Fate has struck down one member of the Strikeforce. Who will be the next? Even as the members of Strikeforce: Morituri confront the consequences of their decision to become super heroes, the rampaging alien Horde unleashes a new menace. The Healers!

17.text: When the Avengers attempt to arrest Magneto so that he may be tried in the World Court for crimes against humanity, the X-Men side with their mutant brother. Can the situation be diffused before the teams come to blows?

24.text: Face the future with Joey and Top Dog! And this timeline is a world gone mad!

25.text: Sunspot has a temper as hot as the sun, but could it cause him to turn against his friends and the X-Men's fight for the greater good?

26.text: Mephisto tries to abduct one member of the Fantastic Four after another into his realm, forcing Sue to make a difficult choice.

27.text: Nightmask navigates a painful family situation when he helps a father come out of a coma after his son tried to kill him.

29.text: Doctor Doom claims the world! Thanks to a power-amplifying boost from the nefarious Purple Man, God Emperor Doom turns the human population, including the Avengers, into his mind slaves!

42.text: Cyclops’ hard times continue in the aftermath to his search for Madelyne Pryor.

47.text: A man who once worked for the mob is trapped in a self-induced coma. With his remarkable psychic abilities, Keith helps the man come back to reality to conquer his guilt.

49.text: The Thorn Monster is on the loose on Endor!

50.text: The pair finally gets some answers regarding the drug ring, but their search is not without casualties. Finale issue!

55.text: Fame glorifies the Strikeforce when a dramatic comic book of their adventures is released and a Strikeforce television program is announced! But the invading alien Horde has its own death-dealing plans for the star-studded hoopla.

60.text: REVENGE The Avengers must reclaim what is rightfully theirs: The Avengers Mansion! But first, The Wasp must find her teammates!

62.text: Wong and Topaz, transported to Urthona's realm! Doctor Strange must rescue two loyal comrades from the gaping jaws of Urthona! But will Strange arrive too late?

73.text: Cyclops goes looking for his ex-wife and son only to find an old enemy!

79.text: As Keith Remsen sleeps, Nightmask springs into battle! This time, he’s warding off a “dream vampire” who’s trying to learn the details of his sleep patterns to report back to Kleinmann.

80.text: While Dakota battles Sheik Ibn Bheik, SJ realizes the identity of the architect behind the plan to steal the nerve gas.
